<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1437,366,897]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[268,517,583,609]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="317 - 338" refId="ref370207" refString="Rondani, C. (1871 a) Diptera italica non vel minus cognita descripta aut annotata. Fasc. IV. Addenda Anthomynis Prodr. Vol. VI. Bullettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 2 (4) [1870], 317 - 338." type="journal article" year="1871">Rondani (1871a: 328)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[642,873,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Corthophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grisella">
<emphasis box="[642,873,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Corthophila grisella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from just the male sex, without specifying either the 
<taxonomicName box="[240,326,619,645]" family="Number" pageId="42" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
or the length of the specimens: “ 
<emphasis box="[692,931,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Marem tantum inveni</emphasis>
[I found the male only]”. In his redescription of the species 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[360,608,655,681]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" refId="ref371380" refString="Rondani, C. (1877 c) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol. VI. Species italicae ordinis dipterorum ordinatim dispositae, methodo analitica distinctae, et novis vel minus cognitis descriptis. Pars quinta. Stirps XVII - Anthomyinae. Societatis Topographorum. Parmae [= Parma], 304 pp." type="book" year="1877">Rondani (1877c: 220)</bibRefCitation>
reported: “ 
<emphasis box="[736,1359,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
Mares aliquos tantum legi 
<taxonomicName box="[1039,1236,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Ins" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="montuosis" subSpecies="agri">in montuosis agri</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[1244,1359,655,680]" genus="Agri" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="parmensis">parmensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
[I collected only a few males in the Parmese mountains]”. We found 
<specimenCount box="[910,1044,691,717]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="generic" typeStatus="syntype">one syntype</specimenCount>
in this study. An additional MZUF male numbered “1217” and labeled “Asch 5.[1]875” is not included in the type series because it was collected at Asch [= Aš, 
<collectingCountry box="[371,554,762,789]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
] by F. Kowarz and later donated to Rondani (
<bibRefCitation author="Hennig, W." box="[1077,1300,762,789]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="873 - 920" refId="ref353556" refString="Hennig, W. (1974 c) 63 a Anthomyiidae [part]. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der Palaearktischen Region. Band 7 / 1. Lieferung 308. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart, pp. 873 - 920." type="book chapter" year="1974">Hennig 1974c: 905</bibRefCitation>
, Claussen &amp; Thomson 1996: 280). 
<bibRefCitation author="Hennig, W." box="[453,691,799,826]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="145 - 192" refId="ref353083" refString="Hennig, W. (1967 b) 63 a. Anthomyiidae [part]. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der Palaearktischen Region. Band 7 / 1. Lieferung 272. E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart, pp. 145 - 192." type="book chapter" year="1967">Hennig (1967b: 164)</bibRefCitation>
considered the two MZUF males as belonging to the type series. Rondani described this nominal species under the generic name “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1870" box="[942,1079,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Corthophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[942,1079,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Corthophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, which is an “incorrect subsequent spelling of 
<taxonomicName authority="Macquart, 1835" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1835" box="[394,718,870,897]" genus="Chortophila" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[394,531,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Chortophila</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Macquart, P. - J. - M." box="[538,718,870,897]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" refId="ref357717" refString="Macquart, P. - J. - M. (1835) Histoire naturelle des Insectes. Dipteres. Tome deuxieme. N. E. Roret, Paris, 703 + 2 pp., 12 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 14274" type="book" year="1835">Macquart, 1835</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
” (
<bibRefCitation author="O'Hara, J. E. &amp; Cerretti, P. &amp; Pape, T. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L." box="[743,1000,870,897]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 268" refId="ref361577" refString="O'Hara, J. E., Cerretti, P., Pape, T. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L. (2011) Nomenclatural studies toward a world list of Diptera genus-group names. Part II: Camillo Rondani. Zootaxa, 3141, 1 - 268. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3141.1.1" type="journal article" year="2011">
O’Hara 
<emphasis box="[835,892,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">et al.</emphasis>
2011: 65
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
